_Values: What is this...? This doesn’t look right… something's wrong here!
Lylah! There you are! I’ve been looking everywhere for you!
That voice... it sounds just like Miss Mittle. But if it is why does she look like this? I better see what she wants

Point your right controller where you want Lylah to move and press the right touch pad to move her to that spot. 
To speak to characters or graffiti on buildings, stand close to them and press the left touchpad to interact. 
They may be able to give you some insight into your situation or give you information.
I understand… on your way now child. If you need help, just speak to the elder by the fountain, he always knows what’s happening around here.
This can’t be happening… can’t be real. Everything was perfect and then it was like sand falling between my fingers.
We want to help you, you need to get to safety
Hello young one, are you ok? I know you’re going through a hard time and you have a long road ahead of you… But you are capable. You need to escape this darkness that surrounds the city.

It’s called The Sorrow and it poisons and transforms normal people like you into nightmarish creatures like me. If you see more creatures like me, please talk to them. They want to help you understand what’s happening around you. We will tell you the story of the city, and yourself in a way.
Where did you get to? I couldn’t find you anywhere! Nevermind that, you need to go to your Granny's house!
All I know is that she's not looking good, she might be nearing her limit
I knew her time was drawing near, her condition was only worsening recently, but I can't let her go without saying…
Time just kept on slipping away and I just wanted it to stop...

Finally, I want you to remember… life will throw challenges at you and the thought of what you’re going through can make you feel like your head is about to explode. You might not want to face the world and you may find it almost impossible to come to terms with reality, but you just need to keep putting one foot in front of the other until your world stops spinning so fast...
You can see what others can’t. Press the right trigger to enter into Sorrow View to see a different version of reality where pain and grief have been allowed to take control.
While in Sorrow View, speak to other characters in the game to get new info or look around the area to see things differently. Pull the right trigger again to return to normal view.
Remember to check the Sorrow View at each challenge as you may find new information in the different reality.

Just because you deny the truth, it doesn’t change the facts. Denial is living in a world where you you refuse to accept the truth and pushing against the unwanted just pushes away your own growth… Know that it’s impossible to wake someone when they’re pretending to be asleep...

You need to learn to grow and absorb what’s happening to you. Speak with my children and make sense of the message that they’re trying to tell and hopefully you’ll grow as they do.

Sticking your head in the sand… turning a blind eye… it’s all part of the same black hole… it’ll suck you in if you aren’t careful.
You’ll fall into the black hole if you aren’t careful...

Speak with my children and make sense of the message that they’re trying to tell and hopefully you’ll grow as they do.

Try speaking to the graffiti and different NPC’s when you’re in both normal and Sorrow View to learn as much as you can about each puzzle.
Go now, make sure you say what you need to say… and remember, the elder by the fountain can help if you need it.
